</p></section><section id="GUID-1F928ED0-FAEA-4F79-ACD8-FE14F662CC05" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Summary</title><p class="- topic/p ">This bulletin describes 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Modification 10</b> for the Colorado M-series: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Height Adjustment Check.</b> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-63453375-8C1D-4A18-905B-B3618C766D9F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">1 Reason</title><p class="- topic/p ">In the factory, a potential measurement error has been detected during the height adjustment check on certain machines. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Some machines were recalled for correction, and it was determined that these machines were within specification in terms of parts and adjustment. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Consequently, the prevailing expectation is that this discrepancy is merely a measurement error within the factory. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However, given the potential risks, it is crucial to verify this. If left unverified, it could lead to challenging print quality issues. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As a precautionary measure, we recommend re-adjusting the printhead gap height for the identified systems (please refer to chapter 2 for a complete list). 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1CB905AD-7F73-420F-9490-A7FA9D45324D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">2 Description</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printhead gap height adjustment is a standard procedure described in the TSM. 
